data.chText: 支架；架子
data.enText: a piece of equipment, usually made of metal or wooden bars, that is used for holding things or for hanging things on

data.chText: 蔬菜 / 酒瓶 / 盘碟 / 面包片架
data.enText: a vegetable/wine/plate/toast rack

data.chText: 我看遍了挂在商店尽里面的一架子衣服。
data.enText: I looked through a rack of clothes at the back of the shop.

data.chText: （旧时的）拉肢刑具
data.enText: an instrument of torture , used in the past for punishing and hurting people. Their arms and legs were tied to the wooden frame and then pulled in opposite directions, stretching the body.

data.chText: （羊、猪等带前肋的）颈脊肉
data.enText: a particular piece of meat that includes the front ribs and is cooked in the oven

data.chText: （机器的）齿条，齿轨
data.enText: a part of a machine that consists of a bar with parts that a wheel or gear can fit into

data.chText: 倍感压力；焦虑万分；痛苦不堪

wrack

data.chText: 使痛苦不堪；使受折磨
data.enText: to make sb suffer great physical or mental pain

data.chText: 深感内疚
data.enText: to be racked with/by guilt

data.chText: 她满脸的痛苦。
data.enText: Her face was racked with pain.

data.chText: 剧烈的抽泣使她全身抽搐。
data.enText: Violent sobs racked her whole body.

data.chText: 剧烈的咳嗽
data.enText: a racking cough
rack your brain(s)

data.chText: 绞尽脑汁；冥思苦想
data.enText: to think very hard or for a long time about sth

data.chText: 她绞尽脑汁，想要回忆起她到底说过些什么话。
data.enText: She racked her brains, trying to remember exactly what she had said.
rack up sth

data.chText: 累积；聚集（某物）；累计（得分）
data.enText: to collect sth, such as profits or losses in a business, or points in a competition

data.chText: 公司两年内损失累计达2亿元。
data.enText: The company racked up $200 million in losses in two years.

data.chText: 在十年的拳击生涯中，他创纪录地累计获胜176次。
data.enText: In ten years of boxing he racked up a record 176 wins.

trans: （企业）大量实现（利润、销售），惨遭（亏损）；（选手或运动队）频频获得（胜利）

tr: a rapid gait of a horse in which each foot strikes the ground separately
a form of torture in which pain is inflicted by stretching the body
a support for displaying various articles
example: the newspapers were arranged on a rack

tr: an instrument of torture that stretches or disjoints or mutilates victims
the destruction or collapse of something
rib section of a forequarter of veal or pork or especially lamb or mutton
seize together, as of parallel ropes of a tackle in order to prevent running through the block

example: They extorted money from the executive by threatening to reveal his past to the company boss
They squeezed money from the owner of the business by threatening him

tr: put on a rack and pinion

value.boxr_value: The spelling wrack is also used, mainly for meanings 2 and 3, and mainly in old-fashioned or American English. 亦拼作wrack，主要用于义项2和3，多见于过时英语或美国英语中。

value.def: A rack is a frame or shelf, usually with bars or hooks, that is used for holding things or for hanging things on.

example.ex: My rucksack was too big for the luggage rack...
example.tran: 我的背包太大了，行李架上放不下。

example.ex: You have to fight to reach the racks of clothes but the bargains are amazing.
example.tran: 你得费力往前挤才能够到那一架架的衣服，但那些打折品的确超值。

value.def: If someone is racked by something such as illness or anxiety, it causes them great suffering or pain.

example.ex: His already infirm body was racked by high fever...
example.tran: 他已经很虚弱的身体受着高烧的折磨。

example.ex: The country is now racked by three violent separatist movements.
example.tran: 这个国家目前正被3场激烈的分离主义运动所困扰。

example.ex: ...a teenager racked with guilt and anxiety.
example.tran: 被愧疚和不安所折磨的少年

value.def: If you rack your brains, you try very hard to think of something.

example.ex: She began to rack her brains to remember what had happened at the nursing home.
example.tran: 她开始绞尽脑汁地回忆在疗养院发生的事。

value.def: If you say that someone is on the rack, you mean that they are suffering either physically or mentally.

example.ex: Only a year ago, he was on the rack with a heroin addiction that began when he was 13.
example.tran: 就在一年前，他还被13岁时开始染上的海洛因毒瘾所折磨。

value.def: If you say that a place is going to rack and ruin, you are emphasizing that it is slowly becoming less attractive or less pleasant because no-one is bothering to look after it.
Off-the-rack clothes or goods are made in large numbers, rather than being made specially for a particular person.

example.ex: ...the same off-the-rack dress she's been wearing since the night before...
example.tran: 她从昨晚就一直穿着的同一件成品裙装

example.ex: For our clothes, we went to a shop on Hollywood Boulevard, and we just picked it all off the rack.
example.tran: 至于衣服，我们到好莱坞大道上的一家商店里，都是直接挑现成的买。

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用 off-the-peg
